1
00:00:48,680 --> 00:00:50,318
<i>You got him! You got him!</i>

2
00:01:03,840 --> 00:01:06,957
<i>Only ever met one man I wouldn't want to fight.</i>

3
00:01:07,040 --> 00:01:08,393
I can't stop that.

4
00:01:08,480 --> 00:01:10,311
Here. Get out of here, you useless tit.

5
00:01:10,400 --> 00:01:13,517
<i>When I met him, he was already
the best cut man in the business.</i>

6
00:01:13,600 --> 00:01:14,794
Can you stop it?

7
00:01:14,880 --> 00:01:18,350
<i>Started training and managing in the '60s,
but he never lost his gift.</i>

8
00:01:18,440 --> 00:01:19,475
No.

9
00:01:27,400 --> 00:01:29,231
Let me have a look at him.

10
00:01:29,320 --> 00:01:31,038
He's fine. He's fine.

11
00:01:31,120 --> 00:01:33,315
Well, he ain't if you don't stop this bleeding.

12
00:01:33,400 --> 00:01:34,879
I'll give you one more round.

13
00:01:35,920 --> 00:01:37,478
Seconds out. Let's go.

14
00:01:37,560 --> 00:01:39,755
What do we do? Tell me what to do.

15
00:01:39,840 --> 00:01:41,876
You let him hit you.

16
00:01:44,320 --> 00:01:47,153
<i>Sometimes, there's just nothing you can do.</i>

17
00:01:47,920 --> 00:01:50,309
<i>Cut's too wide, too close to the bone...</i>

18
00:01:51,640 --> 00:01:53,232
<i>Maybe you got a severed vein...</i>

19
00:01:53,320 --> 00:01:56,471
<i>or you just can't get the coagulant deep enough.</i>

20
00:01:58,360 --> 00:02:01,511
<i>There are all kinds
of combinations you come up against</i>

21
00:02:01,600 --> 00:02:03,989
<i>down in the different layers of meat,</i>

22
00:02:04,080 --> 00:02:05,991
<i>and Frankie knew how to work every one.</i>

23
00:02:30,840 --> 00:02:33,752
<i>People love violence.</i>

24
00:02:34,280 --> 00:02:36,874
<i>They slow down at a car wreck
to check for bodies.</i>

25
00:02:36,920 --> 00:02:39,195
<i>Same people claim to love boxing.</i>

26
00:02:39,280 --> 00:02:41,953
<i>They got no idea what it is.</i>

27
00:02:42,040 --> 00:02:44,190
<i>Boxing is about respect-</i>

28
00:02:44,280 --> 00:02:46,111
<i>getting it for yourself...</i>

29
00:02:46,200 --> 00:02:48,794
<i>...and taking it away from the other guy.</i>

30
00:02:52,920 --> 00:02:54,592
I'll warm up the car.

31
00:02:54,680 --> 00:02:56,193
Mr Dunn?

32
00:02:56,280 --> 00:02:58,271
Hmm. I owe you money?

33
00:02:58,360 --> 00:02:59,554
No, sir.

34
00:02:59,640 --> 00:03:00,993
I know your mama?

35
00:03:01,080 --> 00:03:03,036
Don't rightly know, sir.

36
00:03:03,120 --> 00:03:04,519
Then what is it you want?

37
00:03:04,600 --> 00:03:07,239
I was on the undercard. I won my fight, to0.

38
00:03:07,320 --> 00:03:08,673
Maggie Fitzgerald.

39
00:03:08,760 --> 00:03:11,228
Well, Maggie Fitzgerald, what's up?

40
00:03:11,320 --> 00:03:12,833
Did you happen to see it?

41
00:03:12,920 --> 00:03:15,195
- Nope.
- I did pretty good.

42
00:03:15,280 --> 00:03:17,635
Thought you might
be interested in training me.

43
00:03:17,720 --> 00:03:19,438
I don't train girls.

44
00:03:19,520 --> 00:03:23,229
Maybe you should.
People see me fight say I'm pretty tough.

45
00:03:23,320 --> 00:03:26,073
Girlie, tough ain't enough.

46
00:03:39,400 --> 00:03:41,197
It's a mistake.

47
00:03:46,200 --> 00:03:48,395
Car should be able to back up, Frankie.

48
00:03:48,480 --> 00:03:50,914
Just push, will you?

49
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:52,991
What did Hogan want?

50
00:03:53,080 --> 00:03:54,593
Offered us a title shot.

51
00:03:54,680 --> 00:03:57,797
- 'Bout time.
- I turned him down flat.

52
00:03:57,880 --> 00:04:01,668
Two or three more fights, you'll be ready.

53
00:04:05,720 --> 00:04:09,156
Been two or three more fights
for a long time now, Frankie.

54
00:04:09,240 --> 00:04:11,674
Look, Willie, you get one shot at the title.

55
00:04:11,760 --> 00:04:13,751
You lose it, it may not come around again.

56
00:04:13,840 --> 00:04:17,833
Now, two or three more fights,
and we'll be ready.

57
00:04:17,920 --> 00:04:19,876
Whatever you say, Frankie.

58
00:04:21,240 --> 00:04:25,119
<i>Frankie liked to say
that boxing is an unnatural act,</i>

59
00:04:25,200 --> 00:04:27,919
<i>that everything in boxing is backwards.</i>

60
00:04:30,080 --> 00:04:32,036
<i>Sometimes...</i>

61
00:04:32,120 --> 00:04:34,315
<i>best way to deliver a punch is step back.</i>

62
00:04:43,160 --> 00:04:48,359
Well, do your best, Lord, to... protect Katy.

63
00:04:48,440 --> 00:04:50,192
Annie, to0.

64
00:04:51,320 --> 00:04:54,437
Other than that... you know what I want.

65
00:04:54,520 --> 00:04:57,159
There's no use me repeating myself.

66
00:04:57,240 --> 00:05:01,836
<i>But step back too far, you ain't fightin' at all.</i>

67
00:05:15,440 --> 00:05:17,396
Thank you for your prayers.

68
00:05:17,480 --> 00:05:19,436
- Bye.
- Goodbye.

69
00:05:19,520 --> 00:05:21,909
Hey, Father, that was a great sermon.

70
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:23,399
Made me weep.

71
00:05:23,480 --> 00:05:25,152
What's confusing you this week?

72
00:05:25,240 --> 00:05:27,708
Oh, it's the same old one God, three God thing.

73
00:05:27,800 --> 00:05:30,917
Frankie, most people figure out
by kindergarten it's about faith.

74
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:35,391
Is it sort of like Snap, Crackle and Pop
all rolled up in one big box?

75
00:05:35,480 --> 00:05:39,598
You're standing outside my church
comparing God to Rice Krispies?

76
00:05:39,680 --> 00:05:43,389
You only come to Mass every day to wind me
up. It's not going to happen this morning.

77
00:05:43,480 --> 00:05:44,549
Well, I'm confused.

78
00:05:44,640 --> 00:05:45,993
- No, you aren't.
- Yes, I am.

79
00:05:46,080 --> 00:05:48,958
Then here's your answer: There's one God.

80
00:05:49,040 --> 00:05:50,792
Anything else? Cos I'm busy.

81
00:05:50,880 --> 00:05:53,474
- What about the Holy Ghost?
- An expression of God's love.

82
00:05:53,560 --> 00:05:55,949
- And Jesus?
- Son of God. Don't play stupid.

83
00:05:56,040 --> 00:05:58,759
Well, what is he, then?
Does that make him a demigod?

84
00:05:58,840 --> 00:06:01,229
<i>There are no demigods, you fuckin' pagan!</i>

85
00:06:06,200 --> 00:06:08,031
Did you write to your daughter?

86
00:06:08,120 --> 00:06:09,155
<i>Absolutely.</i>

87
00:06:09,240 --> 00:06:12,357
Now you're lying to a priest.
You know what? Take a day off.

88
00:06:12,440 --> 00:06:14,396
Don't come to Mass tomorrow.

89
00:06:23,160 --> 00:06:27,676
<i>Some people'd say the most
important thing a fighter can have is heart.</i>

90
00:06:28,760 --> 00:06:32,036
<i>Frankie'd say,
"Show me a fighter with nothing but a heart</i>

91
00:06:32,120 --> 00:06:34,953
<i>and I'll show you a man waiting for a beating. "</i>

92
00:06:42,680 --> 00:06:46,229
<i>Think I only ever met one fighter
who was all heart.</i>

93
00:06:47,320 --> 00:06:49,311
My name's Dangerous Dillard

94
00:06:49,400 --> 00:06:53,518
<i>Fightin' Flippo Bam-Bam Barch
Out of Broward County, Texas!</i>

95
00:06:55,160 --> 00:06:58,391
<i>Danger showed up a couple of years back.</i>

96
00:06:59,480 --> 00:07:04,349
<i>He'd come visiting L.A. with Ervel,
his mama's new boyfriend.</i>

97
00:07:04,440 --> 00:07:09,468
<i>Apparently, Ervel got lost
and ended up back in Texas.</i>

98
00:07:09,560 --> 00:07:14,634
<i>Danger looked for him for about a week
'fore he introduced himself.</i>

99
00:07:15,800 --> 00:07:20,715
Hey. You know, I gots nothin' against niggers...

100
00:07:22,200 --> 00:07:23,918
Well, that's nice to hear.

101
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:25,353
Yeah. Yeah.

102
00:07:25,440 --> 00:07:28,591
Lots of people where I comes from does,

103
00:07:28,680 --> 00:07:33,629
but my mama taught me not to cause hurt
to no man, niggers or not.

104
00:07:33,720 --> 00:07:36,678
You got a nice mama.
Anything else I can do for you?

105
00:07:36,760 --> 00:07:40,799
<i>Just one of those questions,
but Danger wanted to give it his best answer.</i>

106
00:07:40,880 --> 00:07:45,271
Well, sir, I'd likes to become
the Welterweight Champion of the world.

107
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:52,033
And I challenge the Motor City Cobra,
Thomas "Hit Man" Hearns,

108
00:07:52,120 --> 00:07:56,159
<i>to fight me for the Welterweight
Championship of the whole world!</i>

109
00:07:56,240 --> 00:07:58,834
<i>Yo, Flip, shut up, man! You ain't even ranked.</i>

110
00:07:58,880 --> 00:08:01,713
You got to have at least one fight to be ranked.

111
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:03,711
<i>Hey, I'll fight any man, anytime!</i>

112
00:08:03,800 --> 00:08:05,472
<i>Hey, you a bad man, huh?</i>

113
00:08:05,560 --> 00:08:08,199
Hey, come on, get in the ring.
Go a round with me.

114
00:08:08,280 --> 00:08:09,633
Shawrelle...

115
00:08:09,720 --> 00:08:11,073
I will.

116
00:08:11,160 --> 00:08:12,434
Leave him alone.

117
00:08:14,040 --> 00:08:16,679
Danger, you goon back to training.

118
00:08:16,760 --> 00:08:18,910
Will do, Mr Scrap.

119
00:08:21,160 --> 00:08:22,593
<i>Ow!</i>

120
00:08:22,680 --> 00:08:24,432
Them some nice tights, Danger.

121
00:08:25,520 --> 00:08:27,875
I'll give you that ass-whoopin' later, Olive Oyl.

122
00:08:27,960 --> 00:08:30,110
<i>Those pants look real pretty on you, bro.</i>

123
00:08:30,200 --> 00:08:32,191
Give his mama back her tights.

124
00:08:32,280 --> 00:08:36,034
<i>Shawrelle Berry
had a left hook that would move a tank...</i>

125
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:39,157
<i>but he had a heart the size of a split pea.</i>

126
00:08:39,240 --> 00:08:43,233
<i>Frankie bought the Hit Pit
from Bobby Malone 17 years ago.</i>

127
00:08:43,320 --> 00:08:46,517
<i>Bobby wanted to move to Florida,
and Frankie wanted some security.</i>

128
00:08:46,600 --> 00:08:49,319
<i>Bobby died while he was packing.</i>

129
00:08:49,400 --> 00:08:53,154
<i>Frankie found out... most gyms lose money.</i>

130
00:08:53,240 --> 00:08:56,312
I thought I told you I didn't want Danger
working out here anymore.

131
00:08:56,400 --> 00:08:58,311
Oh, he ain't hurtin' nothin', Frankie.

132
00:08:58,400 --> 00:09:00,038
Well, he's hurtin' me.

133
00:09:00,120 --> 00:09:04,671
Breakin' my heart watchin' him
punch the air like it's going to punch back.

134
00:09:04,760 --> 00:09:07,513
And how many times have I got to
tell you that bleach is bleach?

135
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:09,318
Why can't you just buy the cheap stuff?

136
00:09:09,400 --> 00:09:11,550
You don't always have to buy expensive stuff.

137
00:09:11,640 --> 00:09:13,517
It smells better, Frankie.

138
00:09:13,600 --> 00:09:16,637
Bleach smells like bleach.

139
00:09:24,560 --> 00:09:25,629
Hey, Scrap.

140
00:09:25,720 --> 00:09:27,438
Hey, Mr Willie.

141
00:09:29,880 --> 00:09:31,836
Hey, nice fight last night.

142
00:09:40,080 --> 00:09:41,354
Big Willie.

143
00:09:41,440 --> 00:09:42,555
Hey, Sally.

144
00:09:45,880 --> 00:09:47,279
- Nice fight.
- Thanks, man.

145
00:09:47,360 --> 00:09:49,032
People are talkin'.

146
00:09:58,560 --> 00:10:03,031
"Ta cul fionn is dha shuil ghlasa agat".

147
00:10:03,120 --> 00:10:05,714
What the hell kind of language is that?

148
00:10:06,640 --> 00:10:08,232
What do you want?

149
00:10:08,320 --> 00:10:10,754
I just thought you might like to know

150
00:10:10,840 --> 00:10:13,798
you got a fighter out there
not talking to another manager.

151
00:10:13,880 --> 00:10:17,634
Not talking to another manager?

152
00:10:17,720 --> 00:10:18,994
Not just any manager.

153
00:10:20,400 --> 00:10:21,594
Mickey Mack.

154
00:10:22,640 --> 00:10:27,509
You came in here to tell me
that Big Willie is not talking to Mickey Mack.

155
00:10:27,600 --> 00:10:30,034
Not a word. Neither one of 'em.

156
00:10:31,160 --> 00:10:33,116
I'm trying to read here.

157
00:10:33,200 --> 00:10:35,475
Well, if you think that's more important...

158
00:10:36,840 --> 00:10:39,115
Who's your new girl?

159
00:10:40,160 --> 00:10:42,310
What?

160
00:10:52,120 --> 00:10:53,792
Jesus Christ.

161
00:10:53,880 --> 00:10:55,233
Better hurry up.

162
00:10:55,320 --> 00:10:58,312
If she keeps hitting it like that,
she gonna break her wrists.

163
00:11:05,880 --> 00:11:07,552
<i>You're wasting your time.</i>

164
00:11:07,640 --> 00:11:10,757
<i>- I told you I don't train girls.
- Thought you might change your mind.</i>

165
00:11:10,840 --> 00:11:13,149
There's dozens of trainers who train girls.

166
00:11:13,240 --> 00:11:15,071
You won't have any trouble finding one.

167
00:11:15,160 --> 00:11:17,355
Don't hardly need a dozen, boss. You'll do fine.

168
00:11:17,440 --> 00:11:21,228
Don't call me boss, now. I'm not your boss,
and don't you be calling me that.

169
00:11:21,320 --> 00:11:24,039
<i>- Willie, you ready to work?
- Anytime.</i>

170
00:11:24,120 --> 00:11:26,714
If I stop calling you boss, will you train me?

171
00:11:26,760 --> 00:11:27,954
No.

172
00:11:29,080 --> 00:11:30,911
I might as well just keep calling you it.

173
00:11:31,960 --> 00:11:34,918
<i>She came from
southwestern Missouri...</i>

174
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:39,152
<i>the hills outside
the scratch-ass Ozark town of Theodosia,</i>

175
00:11:39,240 --> 00:11:44,030
<i>set in the cedars and oak trees somewhere
between nowhere and good-bye.</i>

176
00:11:44,120 --> 00:11:46,634
<i>She grew up knowing one thing:</i>

177
00:11:46,720 --> 00:11:48,472
<i>She was trash.</i>

178
00:12:01,680 --> 00:12:02,908
It's for my dog.

179
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:08,393
<i>She'd come 1,800 miles,
but Theodosia was still just over the hill.</i>

180
00:12:25,720 --> 00:12:27,392
Workin' the bag, boss.

181
00:12:27,480 --> 00:12:30,119
Not your boss... and that bag's working you.

182
00:12:44,200 --> 00:12:46,077
Give her her money back.

183
00:12:47,160 --> 00:12:49,310
You sure?

184
00:12:49,400 --> 00:12:51,231
How much did she pay?

185
00:12:51,320 --> 00:12:52,514
<i>Six months.</i>

186
00:12:52,600 --> 00:12:54,192
Oh, Jesus Christ.

187
00:12:54,280 --> 00:12:55,793
<i>No, I'll just give it back.</i>

188
00:12:55,880 --> 00:12:58,269
No. Don't be a smart-ass now, will you?

189
00:12:58,360 --> 00:13:02,592
Woman thinks I'd throw away six months' dues
just to get rid of her, she's out of her mind.

190
00:13:02,680 --> 00:13:05,956
- But just don't encourage her, understand?
- OK.

191
00:13:06,040 --> 00:13:08,076
And... And what's Danger doing out there?

192
00:13:08,160 --> 00:13:10,230
<i>What's he lookin' at?</i>

193
00:13:14,840 --> 00:13:16,193
Looks like a bottle of water.

194
00:13:16,280 --> 00:13:18,635
He paid his dues?

195
00:13:18,720 --> 00:13:20,517
Dues?

196
00:13:20,600 --> 00:13:23,114
Boy can't afford pants. Want him to pay dues?

197
00:13:23,200 --> 00:13:25,316
Get out of my office.

198
00:13:35,120 --> 00:13:36,599
Fuck me.

199
00:14:20,600 --> 00:14:22,318
Can't think of it as a bag.

200
00:14:25,840 --> 00:14:27,717
I'm not a trainer,

201
00:14:27,800 --> 00:14:29,631
but I can show you this, if you'd like.

202
00:14:29,720 --> 00:14:31,233
Appreciate any help I can get.

203
00:14:31,320 --> 00:14:33,788
OK. Let's see.

204
00:14:33,880 --> 00:14:36,838
What you want to do is
you want to think of it as a man, see?

205
00:14:36,920 --> 00:14:38,273
And he's constantly moving.

206
00:14:38,360 --> 00:14:42,911
He's moving towards you. He's moving around
you. He's moving away from you, all right?

207
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:45,389
You don't want to hit him
when he's coming towards you

208
00:14:45,480 --> 00:14:47,391
cos what he's going to do is push you back.

209
00:14:47,480 --> 00:14:51,393
He's going to smother your punches,
take your balance, right?

210
00:14:51,480 --> 00:14:54,631
So watch him carefully.
Keep rotating, that keeps your head moving,

211
00:14:54,720 --> 00:14:58,429
and keep one shoulder back
so you're always ready to fire a power shot.

212
00:14:58,520 --> 00:14:59,873
Right? Go ahead, now.

213
00:14:59,960 --> 00:15:01,632
Good, good. Keep rotating.

214
00:15:01,720 --> 00:15:03,711
Keep moving. That's it.

215
00:15:03,800 --> 00:15:06,758
Good, good. Keep that chin tucked in.

216
00:15:06,840 --> 00:15:08,512
Come on around.

217
00:15:08,600 --> 00:15:10,272
Keep moving, keep moving.

218
00:15:10,360 --> 00:15:11,554
Good, good, good, good.

219
00:15:11,640 --> 00:15:14,791
- Like that?
- Yeah. Keep on moving, give it a few shots.

220
00:15:15,960 --> 00:15:18,235
Tuck that chin in, now. Tuck that chin in.

221
00:15:19,760 --> 00:15:21,955
<i>That's good. That's good.</i>

222
00:15:22,040 --> 00:15:25,749
Now, you get this down,
we'll put you on the speed bag.

223
00:15:28,720 --> 00:15:30,551
You do have a speed bag?

224
00:15:40,600 --> 00:15:43,239
I'll just borrow it till I can buy my own.

225
00:15:43,320 --> 00:15:45,151
All right, you goon home now.

226
00:15:45,240 --> 00:15:46,593
I'll walk out with you?

227
00:15:46,680 --> 00:15:49,148
No, I am home. Want to see?

228
00:15:49,240 --> 00:15:50,639
Yeah.

229
00:15:58,600 --> 00:16:00,352
It's nice.

230
00:16:02,800 --> 00:16:05,155
Would it bother you much
if I worked a little longer?

231
00:16:05,240 --> 00:16:07,231
No, just...

232
00:16:07,320 --> 00:16:09,550
pull the door closed when you leave.

233
00:16:11,760 --> 00:16:13,716
Thank you.

234
00:16:28,120 --> 00:16:30,554
<i>If there's magic in boxing,</i>

235
00:16:30,640 --> 00:16:34,428
<i>it's the magic of fighting battles
beyond endurance,</i>

236
00:16:34,520 --> 00:16:39,435
<i>beyond cracked ribs, ruptured kidneys
and detached retinas.</i>

237
00:16:49,040 --> 00:16:53,670
<i>It's the magic of risking everything
for a dream that nobody sees but you.</i>

238
00:17:03,360 --> 00:17:05,635
<i>OK, come on. Watch the footwork.</i>

239
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:27,638
Hey, Flip.

240
00:17:27,720 --> 00:17:29,551
Hey, Flippy, come here, man.

241
00:17:29,640 --> 00:17:31,915
