483
00:32:17,960 --> 00:32:21,350
If you're not interested,
then I got more celebrating to do.

484
00:32:23,240 --> 00:32:25,310
Stop, stop, stop.

485
00:32:25,400 --> 00:32:27,152
Goddamn it, stop.

486
00:32:28,120 --> 00:32:29,633
What the hell are you doing?

487
00:32:32,960 --> 00:32:34,632
OK.

488
00:32:34,720 --> 00:32:37,029
If I'm going to take you on...

489
00:32:37,120 --> 00:32:38,633
You won't never regret it.

490
00:32:38,720 --> 00:32:39,948
Look, just listen to me.

491
00:32:40,040 --> 00:32:42,838
- If I take you on...
- I promise I'll work so hard.

492
00:32:42,920 --> 00:32:45,309
God, this is a mistake already.

493
00:32:45,400 --> 00:32:48,756
Mm-mm. I'm listening, boss.

494
00:32:48,840 --> 00:32:52,116
If I take you on, you don't say anything.

495
00:32:52,200 --> 00:32:53,952
You don't question me.

496
00:32:54,040 --> 00:32:58,033
You don't ask why, you don't say anything
except maybe, "Yes, Frankie".

497
00:32:58,120 --> 00:33:01,192
<i>And I'm going to try to forget
the fact that you're a girl.</i>

498
00:33:01,280 --> 00:33:02,508
It's all I ask.

499
00:33:02,600 --> 00:33:05,068
And don't come crying to me if you get hurt.

500
00:33:05,160 --> 00:33:07,754
<i>- All righty.
- We got a deal.</i>

501
00:33:07,800 --> 00:33:09,791
No, not quite.

502
00:33:09,880 --> 00:33:12,030
I'm going to teach you how to fight.

503
00:33:12,120 --> 00:33:14,759
Then, we'll get you a manager,
and I'm off down the road.

504
00:33:14,840 --> 00:33:16,432
I hate to argue with you, but...

505
00:33:16,520 --> 00:33:18,590
Don't argue, it's the only way we're doing it.

506
00:33:18,680 --> 00:33:22,150
I teach you all you need to know, and then
you go off and make a million dollars.

507
00:33:22,240 --> 00:33:25,676
<i>I don't care. You get your teeth
knocked out, I don't care.</i>

508
00:33:25,760 --> 00:33:30,038
I don't want to hear about it either way,
that's how it is. It's the only way I'll do it.

509
00:33:37,840 --> 00:33:39,034
All right.

510
00:33:39,120 --> 00:33:44,274
Now, one of the things I've noticed around
the gym is, you never move your feet.

511
00:33:44,320 --> 00:33:47,471
You stand there just flatfooted.
You've got to move your feet.

512
00:33:47,560 --> 00:33:50,438
That's one of the best things
I'm going to be able to teach you.

513
00:33:50,520 --> 00:33:54,035
So, here's what you do. You get yourself...

514
00:33:54,120 --> 00:33:55,872
Bend your knees a little bit.

515
00:33:55,960 --> 00:33:57,552
Get in an athletic position.

516
00:33:57,640 --> 00:33:59,790
Look like you're going to hit something.

517
00:34:01,960 --> 00:34:04,793
<i>- Move 'em how, boss?
- Uh, just, you go hit the bag.</i>

518
00:34:06,520 --> 00:34:08,238
<i>- Stop.
- What'd I do wrong?</i>

519
00:34:08,320 --> 00:34:10,311
OK, you did two things wrong.

520
00:34:10,400 --> 00:34:13,915
One is you asked a question,
and two is you asked another question.

521
00:34:14,000 --> 00:34:16,230
Now, what I want you to do...

522
00:34:16,320 --> 00:34:18,072
It's not about hitting it hard.

523
00:34:18,160 --> 00:34:19,718
It's how good you hit it.

524
00:34:19,800 --> 00:34:21,631
So, watch me.

525
00:34:21,720 --> 00:34:24,314
And you can count with me if you want,
just count;

526
00:34:24,360 --> 00:34:26,430
On a one count, I hit right through the bag.

527
00:34:26,520 --> 00:34:28,590
- Can you show me that again?
- You just...

528
00:34:28,680 --> 00:34:30,750
Just say "one", please.

529
00:34:30,840 --> 00:34:32,432
<i>- One.
- OK, one.</i>

530
00:34:32,520 --> 00:34:34,112
- One.
- OK.

531
00:34:34,200 --> 00:34:37,317
Yeah, just say one.
That's good. That's good.

532
00:34:37,400 --> 00:34:39,356
Then I move over to my right foot.

533
00:34:39,440 --> 00:34:42,159
You'll see my weight is
shifting to my right foot.

534
00:34:42,240 --> 00:34:46,836
Then I hit it with the back of my hand,
sort of like I'm chipping ice with an ice pick.

535
00:34:46,920 --> 00:34:48,319
Then I come over,

536
00:34:48,400 --> 00:34:51,756
and I shift to my left foot,
and I hit it with my right hand.

537
00:34:53,680 --> 00:34:58,356
And ice pick manoeuvre again, and I come
over on my right foot and hit it right, left.

538
00:34:59,360 --> 00:35:01,749
Don't watch anything but my feet.

539
00:35:02,840 --> 00:35:04,398
One, two, three...

540
00:35:12,960 --> 00:35:15,599
Just do it like that. Just keep practising.

541
00:35:45,440 --> 00:35:50,036
<i>Need to show 'em how to
stand, keep their legs under their shoulders.</i>

542
00:35:56,960 --> 00:36:00,589
<i>To make a fighter,
you got to strip 'em down to bare wood.</i>

543
00:36:00,680 --> 00:36:02,113
Rest when you're dead.

544
00:36:02,200 --> 00:36:03,918
Come here.

545
00:36:07,120 --> 00:36:10,908
<i>You can't just tell 'em
to "forget everything you know".</i>

546
00:36:11,000 --> 00:36:13,355
<i>You got to make 'em forget it in their bones.</i>

547
00:36:13,440 --> 00:36:15,954
Left uppercut, left, left.

548
00:36:17,720 --> 00:36:20,678
<i>Make 'em so tired they only listen to you,</i>

549
00:36:20,760 --> 00:36:24,514
<i>only hear your voice,
only do what you say and nothing else.</i>

550
00:36:24,640 --> 00:36:25,755
Move your feet.

551
00:36:25,840 --> 00:36:28,070
Move your feet around. Let's see you go.

552
00:36:41,120 --> 00:36:43,714
<i>Show 'em how to keep their balance</i>

553
00:36:43,800 --> 00:36:45,472
<i>and take it away from the other guy.</i>

554
00:36:45,560 --> 00:36:47,073
Not so low. Look at me.

555
00:36:47,160 --> 00:36:49,037
Right hook and just turn right over...

556
00:36:52,920 --> 00:36:56,196
<i>How to generate
momentum off your right toe...</i>

557
00:36:57,440 --> 00:37:00,557
<i>...and how to flex your knees
when you fire a jab.</i>

558
00:37:05,920 --> 00:37:07,399
<i>How to fight backing up,</i>

559
00:37:07,480 --> 00:37:10,278
<i>so that the other guy
doesn't want to come after you.</i>

560
00:37:10,360 --> 00:37:12,715
<i>Then you got to show 'em all over again -</i>

561
00:37:12,800 --> 00:37:17,510
<i>over and over and over till they think
they were born that way.</i>

562
00:37:19,800 --> 00:37:22,633
Shift. Shift away. Shift away.

563
00:37:23,640 --> 00:37:26,757
OK, that's enough for today.

564
00:37:26,840 --> 00:37:29,718
Good work. Good girl.

565
00:37:31,840 --> 00:37:34,434
Think I'm ready for a fight, boss?

566
00:37:55,480 --> 00:37:56,959
Hey.

567
00:37:57,040 --> 00:37:58,951
<i>Hey, come here.</i>

568
00:38:01,600 --> 00:38:03,272
You're not breathing.

569
00:38:04,920 --> 00:38:06,512
Hate to disagree with you.

570
00:38:06,600 --> 00:38:09,672
Every time you get under pressure,
you're holding your breath.

571
00:38:09,760 --> 00:38:11,113
Now, stop doing that.

572
00:38:11,200 --> 00:38:12,952
OK.

573
00:38:13,040 --> 00:38:15,634
But other than that, I'm doing pretty good, right?

574
00:38:15,720 --> 00:38:17,870
I mean, for a girl.

575
00:38:17,960 --> 00:38:19,518
I don't train girls.

576
00:38:21,800 --> 00:38:23,950
Think I might be ready for a fight, boss?

577
00:38:24,040 --> 00:38:27,350
Well, we'll get a manager,
and we'll find out, won't we?

578
00:38:27,440 --> 00:38:30,876
I'd like to, but you've
been keeping me to0 busy.

579
00:38:37,080 --> 00:38:38,957
Got any family, boss?

580
00:38:39,040 --> 00:38:40,155
What?

581
00:38:42,600 --> 00:38:45,592
You been spending all this time with me.
I didn't know if you had any.

582
00:38:46,560 --> 00:38:47,993
<i>No.</i>

583
00:38:49,000 --> 00:38:51,958
Well, I've got a daughter - Katy.

584
00:38:52,040 --> 00:38:53,792
That's family.

585
00:38:53,880 --> 00:38:56,599
We're not exactly close.

586
00:38:56,680 --> 00:38:58,398
How much she weigh?

587
00:38:59,400 --> 00:39:00,879
What?

588
00:39:00,960 --> 00:39:03,315
Trouble in my family comes by the pound.

589
00:39:06,120 --> 00:39:07,599
Yeah.

590
00:39:07,680 --> 00:39:10,035
Not very big.

591
00:39:10,120 --> 00:39:12,111
Used to be real athletic.

592
00:39:12,200 --> 00:39:14,270
Don't know if she kept it up.

593
00:39:19,720 --> 00:39:22,473
<i>So... what do you think?</i>

594
00:39:23,560 --> 00:39:25,437
Am I ready for a fight?

595
00:39:30,320 --> 00:39:31,673
Hey, Sally.

596
00:39:34,040 --> 00:39:35,712
Come here for a minute, will you?

597
00:39:37,480 --> 00:39:40,233
Frankie, I need to see you
in the back for a minute, OK?

598
00:39:40,320 --> 00:39:41,673
<i>Can I see you a minute?</i>

599
00:39:41,760 --> 00:39:45,116
Sally here is a real good manager.
Has a couple Golden Glove boys.

600
00:39:45,200 --> 00:39:47,111
Looking for a girl, Sally?

601
00:39:47,200 --> 00:39:49,236
I'm looking for a good one.

602
00:39:50,120 --> 00:39:52,076
Well, see, there you go.

603
00:39:55,280 --> 00:39:57,635
Nice working with you, girlie.

604
00:40:00,760 --> 00:40:02,990
- What'd you want?
- Nothing. It's nothing.

605
00:40:03,080 --> 00:40:07,631
<i>I ain't lying. I been watching you work.
You've got a hell of a left.</i>

606
00:40:07,720 --> 00:40:09,438
Thank you.

607
00:40:11,800 --> 00:40:14,030
So, you want to give this a try, see if it's a fit?

608
00:40:16,640 --> 00:40:18,312
Yeah, sure.

609
00:40:18,400 --> 00:40:22,188
Good... cos I think you're ready for a fight.

610
00:40:25,000 --> 00:40:26,911
All right.

611
00:40:33,920 --> 00:40:35,478
<i>Break!</i>

612
00:40:35,560 --> 00:40:39,030
What am I doing wrong, Sally?
Every time I get inside, she's on me.

613
00:40:39,120 --> 00:40:42,317
You're doing great. You're wearing her down.
Just keep punching.

614
00:40:42,400 --> 00:40:44,152
I ain't doing great. I'm losing.

615
00:40:44,240 --> 00:40:45,912
You're wearing her down.

616
00:41:07,240 --> 00:41:09,231
Nice night, ain't it?

617
00:41:09,320 --> 00:41:11,595
Jesus Christ.

618
00:41:11,680 --> 00:41:14,114
That's Lonnie Washington's girl.

619
00:41:14,200 --> 00:41:17,476
Hell of a fighter. 11 and 0.

620
00:41:17,560 --> 00:41:20,233
Your left. Keep your left up.

621
00:41:24,200 --> 00:41:26,509
Lonnie's got a lot of good fighters.

622
00:41:26,600 --> 00:41:30,036
He's got Joey Adagio, lightweight champ.

623
00:41:30,120 --> 00:41:31,439
Yeah.

624
00:41:31,520 --> 00:41:33,715
<i>Your left, damn it!</i>

625
00:41:33,800 --> 00:41:37,076
Wouldn't have been my choice for a first fight,

626
00:41:37,160 --> 00:41:38,832
but Sally's a good manager.

627
00:41:38,920 --> 00:41:40,751
He must think she can take her.

628
00:41:40,840 --> 00:41:42,558
<i>Jesus H, your left!</i>

629
00:41:42,640 --> 00:41:44,596
<i>Keep your left up!</i>

630
00:41:44,680 --> 00:41:46,830
You think she can hear you from back here?

631
00:41:54,280 --> 00:41:58,034
Of course, if Maggie loses,
it wouldn't mean anything to Sally.

632
00:41:58,120 --> 00:41:59,951
Might even help him.

633
00:42:00,040 --> 00:42:02,031
Lonnie's girl gets another win,

634
00:42:02,120 --> 00:42:06,830
Lonnie might let Sally's lightweight
fight Joey Adagio for the title.

635
00:42:06,920 --> 00:42:09,229
Sally's trying to set a fight with Adagio?

636
00:42:09,320 --> 00:42:10,958
Hey, what do I know?

637
00:42:11,040 --> 00:42:13,554
I just come cos I enjoy the fights.

638
00:42:13,640 --> 00:42:15,278
<i>Mother of God!</i>

639
00:42:16,320 --> 00:42:18,197
<i>OK, break!</i>

640
00:42:18,280 --> 00:42:20,316
<i>Hey! Come here, come here.</i>

641
00:42:20,400 --> 00:42:21,913
<i>Hey, get over here!</i>

642
00:42:22,000 --> 00:42:25,151
You're dropping your left hand.
Quit dropping your left hand.

643
00:42:25,240 --> 00:42:28,118
Hey, Frankie, you mind if I talk to my fighter?

644
00:42:28,200 --> 00:42:31,510
You're doing a hell of a job of it.
Is this how you advise your lightweight?

645
00:42:31,600 --> 00:42:34,592
Dunn, what the hell are you doing?

646
00:42:34,680 --> 00:42:37,035
- I'm talking. What you doing?
- This your fighter?

647
00:42:37,120 --> 00:42:39,076
<i>It's my fighter!</i>

648
00:42:39,160 --> 00:42:41,515
It ain't fitting real well, Sally.

649
00:42:41,600 --> 00:42:45,229
Fine. You take her.
She can't fight worth a shit, anyway.

650
00:42:45,320 --> 00:42:47,072
Somebody tell me what's going on.

651
00:42:47,160 --> 00:42:49,071
I was late. Sally was just subbing for me.

652
00:42:49,160 --> 00:42:51,549
You're telling me this is your fighter?

653
00:42:53,080 --> 00:42:55,958
Yeah, this is my fighter.

654
00:42:56,040 --> 00:42:57,837
Then you got ten seconds.

655
00:42:57,920 --> 00:43:00,639
I keep holding my left up,
then I throw a punch and it drops.

656
00:43:00,720 --> 00:43:02,756
- Well, let it drop.
- That'd be a lot easier.

657
00:43:02,840 --> 00:43:04,478
She thinks she knows you, that's all.

658
00:43:04,560 --> 00:43:06,994
Every time you drop it,
she comes right over the top,

659
00:43:07,080 --> 00:43:08,911
so you just wait for her, see?

660
00:43:09,000 --> 00:43:10,638
That's all she's thinking about.

661
00:43:10,720 --> 00:43:13,029
And when she cocks
that big right hand, you hear me?

662
00:43:13,120 --> 00:43:16,908
And when she does, you step to the side
and come over with this big "good night" hook.

663
00:43:17,000 --> 00:43:18,353
- Got one?
- Got it right here.

664
00:43:18,440 --> 00:43:19,509
OK.

665
00:43:19,600 --> 00:43:22,068
- Fight, or I'm calling it.
- Go give it to her.

666
00:43:22,160 --> 00:43:25,550
<i>The body knows
what fighters don't - how to protect itself.</i>

667
00:43:25,640 --> 00:43:28,279
<i>A neck can only twist so far.</i>

668
00:43:28,360 --> 00:43:31,079
<i>Twist it just a hair more, and the body says,</i>

669
00:43:31,160 --> 00:43:35,597
<i>"Hey, I'll take it from here, cos you obviously
don't know what you're doing".</i>

670
00:43:35,680 --> 00:43:37,238
Neutral corner.

671
00:43:37,320 --> 00:43:38,673
<i>Two, three, four...</i>

672
00:43:38,760 --> 00:43:40,910
- See the way she did that?
- Yeah.

673
00:43:41,000 --> 00:43:43,673
Sugar Ray would do that. Girl's got sugar.

674
00:43:43,760 --> 00:43:49,437
<i>"Lie down, now. Rest, and we'll
talk about this when you regain your senses".</i>

675
00:43:49,520 --> 00:43:51,909
<i>It's called the knockout mechanism.</i>

676
00:43:52,000 --> 00:43:54,639
Don't get all carried away, now. Good girl.

677
00:43:54,720 --> 00:43:56,517
Thanks, boss.

678
00:43:57,600 --> 00:44:00,068
You, uh... You forgot the rule.

679
00:44:00,160 --> 00:44:02,833
- Now, what is the rule?
- Keep my left up?

680
00:44:02,920 --> 00:44:05,639
It's to protect yourself at all times.

681
00:44:05,720 --> 00:44:07,676
Now, what is the rule?

682
00:44:07,760 --> 00:44:09,239
Protect myself at all times.

683
00:44:09,320 --> 00:44:10,878
Good, good.

684
00:44:10,960 --> 00:44:13,349
You gave me away. How's that protecting me?

685
00:44:14,440 --> 00:44:16,078
It wasn't.

686
00:44:17,120 --> 00:44:18,599
It's OK.

687
00:44:18,680 --> 00:44:20,636
I'll work on my left, boss.

688
00:44:20,720 --> 00:44:22,915
Drink your water.

689
00:44:23,000 --> 00:44:25,639
Other than that, how'd I do?

690
00:44:25,720 --> 00:44:28,792
Fine. You did fine.

691
00:44:28,880 --> 00:44:31,189
You gonna leave me again?

692
00:44:33,160 --> 00:44:34,957
Never.

693
00:44:35,040 --> 00:44:39,238
That place you work - do they have
homemade lemon meringue pie there?

694
00:44:39,320 --> 00:44:40,753
Sure.

695
00:44:40,840 --> 00:44:42,876
Not the kind with the canned filling crap?

696
00:44:42,960 --> 00:44:45,997
Oh, big can, yea size.
It says "homemade" on the label.

697
00:44:48,280 --> 00:44:51,272
- I want you to take the weekend off.
- It's only Thursday.

698
00:44:51,360 --> 00:44:53,749
You gonna argue with me?

699
00:44:53,840 --> 00:44:55,956
Know better than to do that, boss.

700
00:44:56,960 --> 00:44:57,915
Good.

701
00:44:58,000 --> 00:45:00,958
<i>All fighters
are pig-headed some way or other.</i>

702
00:45:01,040 --> 00:45:04,476
<i>Some part of them always thinks
they know better than you about something.</i>

703
00:45:04,560 --> 00:45:08,314
Can you uh... spare a few minutes
for the Immaculate Conception?

704
00:45:09,960 --> 00:45:13,714
<i>Truth is, even if they're wrong,</i>

705
00:45:13,800 --> 00:45:16,872
<i>even if that one thing
is going to be the ruin of them,</i>

706
00:45:16,960 --> 00:45:20,077
<i>if you can beat that last bit out of 'em,</i>

707
00:45:20,160 --> 00:45:21,832
<i>then they ain't fighters at all.</i>

708
00:45:21,920 --> 00:45:23,478
Thought I said I'd see you Monday.

709
00:45:23,560 --> 00:45:25,312
You sure did, boss.

710
00:45:25,400 --> 00:45:27,152
That was last night.

711
00:45:27,240 --> 00:45:29,037
You said not to argue with you.

712
00:45:40,960 --> 00:45:43,269
Damn woman won't do a thing I tell her.

713
00:45:43,360 --> 00:45:45,237
You want my advice?

714
00:45:45,320 --> 00:45:46,514
What?

715
00:45:47,400 --> 00:45:49,470
Where are your shoes?

716
00:45:50,560 --> 00:45:52,710
I'm airing out my feet.

717
00:45:53,760 --> 00:45:56,115
You got big holes in your socks.

718
00:45:56,200 --> 00:45:58,395
Oh, they're not that big.

719
00:46:00,880 --> 00:46:02,950
Didn't I give you money for some new ones?

720
00:46:04,040 --> 00:46:06,156
These are my sleeping socks.

721
00:46:07,440 --> 00:46:10,034
<i>My feet like a little air at night.</i>

722
00:46:10,080 --> 00:46:12,753
How come you're wearing 'em
in the daytime, then?

723
00:46:12,840 --> 00:46:15,798
Cos my daytime socks
got to0 many holes in 'em.

724
00:46:17,880 --> 00:46:23,113
Well, if I give you some more money,
you buy some new socks.

725
00:46:23,200 --> 00:46:24,633
Please.

726
00:46:26,760 --> 00:46:30,673
Well, I'd be tempted, but I couldn't say for sure.

727
00:46:30,760 --> 00:46:33,194
Might find its way to the track.

728
00:46:56,360 --> 00:46:58,237
<i>Oh!</i>

729
00:47:05,760 --> 00:47:08,911
<i>Didn't take Maggie long to hit her stride.</i>

730
00:47:19,720 --> 00:47:21,199
I got the breathing thing down.

731
00:47:21,280 --> 00:47:24,829
No, you ain't breathing because you're knocking
'em out in the first round.

732
00:47:24,920 --> 00:47:26,194
Thought that was the point.

733
00:47:26,280 --> 00:47:28,396
The point is to get good.

734
00:47:28,480 --> 00:47:31,278
Can't get good if you keep knocking 'em out
in the first round.

735
00:47:31,360 --> 00:47:32,998
How am I going to get you fights?

736
00:47:35,400 --> 00:47:37,709
Nobody wants to see their fighter embarrassed.

737
00:47:37,800 --> 00:47:40,394
<i>Why am I still doing four-rounders, boss?</i>

738
00:47:40,480 --> 00:47:43,233
Cos you haven't got the lungs for six rounds,
that's why.

739
00:47:43,320 --> 00:47:46,471
I do if I keep knocking 'em
out in the first round.

740
00:47:49,720 --> 00:47:52,917
<i>Frankie made her fight
one more four-rounder...</i>

741
00:47:53,000 --> 00:47:55,434
<i>just to let her know who was boss.</i>

742
00:47:58,760 --> 00:48:01,479
Three, four, five,

743
00:48:01,560 --> 00:48:03,630
<i>six, seven...</i>

744
00:48:03,720 --> 00:48:05,756
Sorry, boss.

745
00:48:05,840 --> 00:48:08,229
<i>Maggie left no doubt about it.</i>

746
00:48:20,560 --> 00:48:24,439
<i>Her first six-rounder
didn't go quite as smooth.</i>

747
00:48:38,800 --> 00:48:41,075
<i>Down!</i>

748
00:48:41,160 --> 00:48:44,072
To the corner. Three, four...

749
00:48:44,160 --> 00:48:45,673
<i>five...</i>

750
00:48:45,760 --> 00:48:47,273
<i>six, seven,</i>

751
00:48:47,360 --> 00:48:48,759
<i>eight...</i>

752
00:48:48,840 --> 00:48:51,035
<i>nine, ten! It's over!</i>

753
00:48:51,120 --> 00:48:54,829
<i>Maggie didn't knock her out
till the end of the first round.</i>

754
00:48:54,920 --> 00:48:59,471
<i>After that, no manager wanted
to put his fighter in with Maggie.</i>

755
00:49:04,120 --> 00:49:07,157
<i>Frankie had to go into his pocket to get her
decent fights,</i>

756
00:49:07,240 --> 00:49:11,233
<i>sweetening the purse
by paying managers on the side.</i>

757
00:49:22,280 --> 00:49:25,078
<i>But that only worked for so long.</i>

758
00:49:25,160 --> 00:49:28,470
<i>Then Frankie did something he hated doing.</i>

759
00:49:28,560 --> 00:49:30,471
<i>He took a chance.</i>

760
00:49:38,200 --> 00:49:40,430
<i>He moved her up in class.</i>

761
00:49:40,520 --> 00:49:42,511
<i>That could've been a mistake.</i>

762
00:50:07,560 --> 00:50:10,518
Break. Break. Step back.

763
00:50:10,600 --> 00:50:11,999
<i>Time.</i>

764
00:50:19,280 --> 00:50:21,555
- Dang.
- Dang.

765
00:50:24,680 --> 00:50:27,558
Hey, give us two seconds, will ya?
Just two seconds.

766
00:50:28,680 --> 00:50:31,114
<i>- Your nose is broke.
- Dang!</i>

767
00:50:31,200 --> 00:50:32,599
- Fix it.
- I can't. I can't.

768
00:50:32,680 --> 00:50:34,079
You can fix it.

769
00:50:34,160 --> 00:50:37,550
- I can't. I've gotta call it.
- I've seen what you can do. Fix it.

770
00:50:37,640 --> 00:50:40,473
I can snap it back into place,
but I can't stop the bleeding.

771
00:50:40,560 --> 00:50:41,993
The ring doctor's gonna call it.

772
00:50:42,080 --> 00:50:44,548
Please. If you can stop the blood, I can beat her.

773
00:50:46,640 --> 00:50:48,517
Bite down on this.

774
00:50:58,440 --> 00:50:59,634
OK.

775
00:51:05,920 --> 00:51:07,035
Inhale.

776
00:51:07,120 --> 00:51:08,155
- What?
- Inhale.

777
00:51:08,240 --> 00:51:09,116
What?

778
00:51:09,200 --> 00:51:10,679
Breathe in.

779
00:51:21,720 --> 00:51:22,709
OK, huh?

780
00:51:22,800 --> 00:51:23,835
Yeah, it's OK.

781
00:51:23,920 --> 00:51:25,069
Yeah. All right.

782
00:51:25,160 --> 00:51:27,390
You got 20 seconds before
this turns into a geyser

783
00:51:27,480 --> 00:51:29,436
and it's gonna spray all over the front row.

784
00:51:29,520 --> 00:51:31,795
20 seconds - that's all you've got.

785
00:51:31,880 --> 00:51:33,108
Get goin'.

786
00:51:46,120 --> 00:51:47,314
<i>Go to your corner!</i>

787
00:51:47,400 --> 00:51:49,038
<i>Two,</i>

788
00:51:49,120 --> 00:51:51,918
<i>three, four, five,</i>

789
00:51:52,000 --> 00:51:53,877
six, seven,

790
00:51:53,960 --> 00:51:55,552
<i>eight,</i>

791
00:51:55,640 --> 00:51:58,234
<i>nine, ten!</i>

792
00:52:00,520 --> 00:52:02,112
"Mo cuishle".

793
00:52:15,520 --> 00:52:17,795
Whatcha reading?

794
00:52:17,880 --> 00:52:20,314
What's she saying?

795
00:52:20,400 --> 00:52:22,436
Wants to know what you're reading.

796
00:52:22,520 --> 00:52:23,873
It's Yeats.

797
00:52:23,960 --> 00:52:26,269
Keep your head back.

798
00:52:26,360 --> 00:52:28,351
Why don't you talk a little Yeats to her?

799
00:52:28,440 --> 00:52:30,396
Show her what a treat that is.

800
00:52:31,320 --> 00:52:33,675
When the hell they gonna get to her?

801
00:52:33,760 --> 00:52:36,035
I'm OK, Frankie.

802
00:52:36,120 --> 00:52:37,792
What'd you learn tonight?

803
00:52:37,880 --> 00:52:39,836
Always protect myself.

804
00:52:39,920 --> 00:52:42,354
- What's the rule?
- Always protect myself.

805
00:52:42,440 --> 00:52:44,954
<i>- Margaret Fitzgerald?
- Here.</i>

806
00:52:48,600 --> 00:52:49,999
I'll be right here.

807
00:53:02,040 --> 00:53:03,598
How you doin'?

808
00:53:03,680 --> 00:53:05,079
- Me?
- Yeah, you.

809
00:53:05,160 --> 00:53:07,037
I'm not the one who's hurt.

810
00:53:11,000 --> 00:53:13,434
Broken nose don't hurt that much.

811
00:53:13,520 --> 00:53:15,590
Why are you telling me that?

812
00:53:17,560 --> 00:53:19,232
No reason.

813
00:53:19,320 --> 00:53:23,916
<i>But some wounds are too deep
or too close to the bone.</i>

814
00:53:24,000 --> 00:53:28,039
<i>And no matter how hard you work at it,
you just can't stop the bleeding.</i>

815
00:53:28,120 --> 00:53:29,838
Did you write your daughter?

816
00:53:29,920 --> 00:53:32,070
Every week.

817
00:53:33,080 --> 00:53:35,230
I've no idea why you come to church.

818
00:54:06,080 --> 00:54:10,756
<i>After her 12th straight knockout,
Frankie got a couple of real good offers.</i>

819
00:54:13,320 --> 00:54:17,518
<i>The first was to fight Billie "The Blue Bear"
Osterman for the WBA welterweight title.</i>

820
00:54:19,760 --> 00:54:21,318
<i>Billie the Blue Bear!</i>

821
00:54:21,400 --> 00:54:24,790
<i>Billie was a former
prostitute out of East Berlin.</i>

822
00:54:24,880 --> 00:54:27,838
<i>Had a reputation for being
the dirtiest fighter in the ranks.</i>

823
00:54:46,680 --> 00:54:49,558
<i>Didn't matter to her
something like that could kill a person.</i>

824
00:54:51,520 --> 00:54:52,919
And the crowds loved her.

825
00:54:56,320 --> 00:54:58,914
<i>He turned it down without even telling her.</i>

826
00:54:58,960 --> 00:55:03,397
<i>The next was to fight the British champ,
a Jamaican girl Billie just beat.</i>

827
00:55:03,480 --> 00:55:04,959
Hello?

828
00:55:05,040 --> 00:55:07,554
Not interested.

829
00:55:10,000 --> 00:55:12,434
<i>He turned that down, too.</i>

830
00:55:14,680 --> 00:55:16,477
That's a lot of money, boss.

831
00:55:16,560 --> 00:55:20,155
Yeah. You're making money.
What're you still working here for?

832
00:55:20,240 --> 00:55:22,071
It's a title match, right?

833
00:55:22,160 --> 00:55:25,391
Are you British? It's a title you can't take away.

834
00:55:25,480 --> 00:55:28,313
She's got nothing to lose,
you got nothing to win.

835
00:55:29,400 --> 00:55:31,311
Might still be a good fight.

836
00:55:31,400 --> 00:55:35,188
Yeah. I ju... I just brought you up to welterweight.

837
00:55:35,280 --> 00:55:38,909
To0 good to fight these contenders,
you'd rather fight some bullshit champ?

838
00:55:39,000 --> 00:55:41,275
Didn't notice I was fighting any contenders.

839
00:55:42,240 --> 00:55:46,074
Well, you can get yourself another manager
any time you want.

840
00:55:46,160 --> 00:55:49,914
In fact, if you'd learnt
to protect your face a little better,

841
00:55:50,000 --> 00:55:51,911
I wouldn't have to turn down this money.

842
00:55:54,920 --> 00:55:59,152
My face out there so much,
it's a miracle I ain't been knocked out yet, boss.

